Clauses 1 and 2 should be incorporated in 1.<br>
What we should think about: What do we want to gain from relations? What do we hope for?<br>
<br>
Section II<br>
3.  Nations must not act through war with other nations unless it is for their own defence. So wed recognize almost all nations, after we get to know them a bit. Nations we would not recognize are out breakers unless the mother-nation recognizes the outbreaking. If mother nation is dead we can recognize the out breaker nation (e.g. Baracão).  For an example if Babkha was experiencing a coup détat, and the Republic of Shahzamin asked for our recognition we would give it unless a) we get to know them, b) Babkha recognizes them (as the case with Ayllu)<br>
Anything else?<br>
<br>
4. Recognition can/should be terminated if a nation unprovoked attacks our nation or another nation. And if the nation plants coups or supports terrorist organizations/activities.  Recognition shall also be terminated if a nation stops recognizing us (as it was with Shireroth)<br>
Any further ideas?<br>
<br>
5. Types of Recognition<br>
Just 2 would work for me, allies and friends. Friends are all nations we have peaceful relations with and allies when we co-operate in defensive and/or political activities.<br>
<br>
Section III<br>
6. A foreign representative is a person who officially speaks on behalf of a nation in Menelmacar. Menelmacar reserves the right to decline a foreign representative; all foreign representatives must be accepted by the Foreign Edification (except for Heads of States, Governments and Foreign Ministers)<br>
<br>
7. Our ambassadors are the only people authorized to speak on behalf of the Menelmacari People. They will be assigned a country where they will act as the Menelmacari Representative. Communiqués/letters/statements of minor status/importance from a representative of Menelmacar will have to be accepted by the Foreign Edification, of major status/importance by the Conclave.<br>
<br>
Section IV<br>
8. *shrugs* <br>
9. Menelmacar could join any organization really, if the Conclave accepts. As long as it doesnt mean that the organization would have any legal authority over us theyre good. If an organization wishes to have legal authority over its members or we join one who has, we would have to put an extra clause in the Government Paper explaining that authority. That means a 3/5 amendment<br>
<br>
10, 11, 12. Menelmacari diplomats in International Organizations/Conventions would on minor issues have to ask the Foreign Edification for their opinion. On major issues, such as a new constitution for an organization, the Conclave will have the last word.<br>
International treaties must be verified by the Conclave before they are adapted in Menelmacar.<br>
<br>
Section V<br>
13. If a nation threatens Menelmacar the Menelmacari Foreign Edification will issue a protest. A counter threat must be accepted by the Conclave of Equals. If a nation attacks Menelmacar through destruction (hacking, spamming, bombs, timebombs), the Foreign Edification will advice the Administrator to temporarily ban the attackers and put the forums on MBA. The Foreign Edification will issue a protest to the attacker nation, either directly or in case we are banned from their community, through a recognized nation of ours we trust.<br>
The Conclave of Equals can if the attacks are severe declare war through a 3/5 vote.  The Menelmacari Police will conduct warfare.<br>
<br>
14. <br>
If there is an unknown attacker on Menelmacar, the Administrator is ordered to put the Forums on MBA, and all applicants shall be shown and discussed.  Menelmacari Police will order an Investigation of the attacks and bring the attackers to justice<br>
<br>
15. If a known terrorist organization, measures are the same as if unknown individuals attack. An investigation shall be ordered.<br>
<br>
Section VI<br>
16. If a recognized nation gets attacked, Menelmacar will offer her sympathies (lol that sounds bad). This needs further debate<br>
<br>
17. Coups détats needs also to be debated.<br>
<br>
This is at no way the agenda, only my ideas. Lets discuss them further!<br>
